                },
                "html": "People in some regions claim to have seen creatures that are just like tatzlwyrms in most respects\u2014a long body, two arms, and a head\u2014except that they have traits that are not of reptilian origin. Travelers on a savanna should beware a furry, lion-headed tatzlwyrm protecting its cubs, while those in the mountains might be attacked by a feathered (but wingless) variant with the head of an eagle."
            }
